reviews.text:
Top quality local bakery cafe aka Cha Chan Ting

Price to quality is best in value compare to other cafe near by

A breakfast set including drinks only ~$5 USD compare to just a coffee elsewhere 

Most important you got to taste the true local way of breakfast if you visiting Hong Kong

Any one should try their cocktail bun with a cup of coffee. It is my opioion they are much better than the other larger mass production bakery.  Plus they price is reasonable.  I phone in my order, and the staff hold them for me at the counter.  Very friendly service.  However, the restaurant seems very busy with a long line.

The baked breads here are really good. I haven’t eaten in the restaurant so I can’t speak for the food. However, if you are in the Wan Chai area this place is worth a visit. 

The pineapple bun is soft and chewy with a crunchy sweet top.  The name is bit misleading as it tastes nothing like pineapple but is still delicious.

Stumbled here after wandering through the Wan Chai Street market. More contemporary exterior and interior look to a traditional HK style cafe. Pretty clean. We just had the buttered Pineapple Buns and it was great. There’s a not so secret secret menu which has some pretty interesting items.

If you're around Wan Chai, definitely give this place a try! They are famous for their Pineapple buns and other baked breads. I have been here several times for breakfast and I can tell you that this place serves authentic, delicious Hong Kong Style Breakfast!

reviews.text:
位置方便，不用排隊。
價錢不斷加，但水準開始下降。
同一碗麵裡，麵質有硬有淋，豬扒煎到乾硬。
檸檬茶叫少甜都好甜。
菠蘿油失準，面個層唔夠脆，個包唔再鬆軟。
明明話可以用apps點餐，原來未準備好。

It is not as good as before, pork chop is tooooo dried, and is hard to chew. The noodle is not well prepared, there's soft and not yet cooked noodle mixed together.
Pineapple bun no longer as attractive as before, is not crunchy on the top crust, and too sticky inside.
Even as I asked for less ice and less sweet, it is just as same as my friend's regular one.
The good thing is there's no longer a long queue to line up and is at a really good location to meet others.
A few special meal sets were available though it was a 'cha chan tang'.  Service was good.
a long queue fast food shop, quite good for Wan Chai district
thought that it’s a high end cha chaan teng from the modern outlook, but it’s super mediocre from service to food quality. not gonna revisit.

Fresh local bakery.  Most items are great.  Lots of variety of foods.
Great affordable joint.

reviews.text: 出爐包👍

D 提子包好軟好食， 但個收銀態度差， 我叫凍檸檬茶走甜， 因飲左覺有甜攞番去換， 個女人話我杯飲過叫我攞走， 冇人會要， 我心唸咩唔係幫我拋落垃圾桶， 我見她比面色我睇， 我話好似我錯咁， 我話唔要啦， 跟住她又即刻話請埋舊個杯我飲， 沖左杯冇甜後我離開， 有甜個杯我行行下想拋， 最後我走番轉頭想退番杯野， 個女人又話又咩事呀， 我話因要搭巴士，唔該她隔離個男人幫我拋。…… 我以後等第二個收銀當值先幫襯

這裏的菠蘿飽確實名不虛傳,摩一吓隻麵飽碟,是暖的,有意誠為個飽保温.飽皮脆的,香的, 飽有彈性不是太空飽. 不過,大家睇睇, 這塊鮮油是否太薄呢? $33套餐,不夠利潤就多收五毫啦, 敗筆 ...可惜...
員工高聲呼叫的溝通方法令冰室很嘈雜, 地方已十分夾窄, 員工又跑來跑去, 係跑, 做成客人頗大滋擾,實在感覺不太良好.
門口一張二張地氈, 尺寸又太大,横横直直的放著,不雅觀. 
烘焙部已十分成功, 裝煌也無問題,只欠樓面令冰室更上一層樓.
可能帶著期望而來, 感覺有點可惜啫

第二次去，塊鮮油就合理番啦！
咖啡好唔好飲唔知😀 食品就真係算價廉物美

大件夾抵食, 菠蘿包鬆軟, 面層既香脆皮甜甜地加片凍牛油, 好食到震。食品種類多, 梗有一款啱你。梗有一款適合你。

The pineapple bun is soft, and the top layer is crispy and sweet, and the frozen butter is added, it's really good.  There are many kinds of food, and there is a stalk of you.

reviews.text:
新派茶餐室。有地下和閣樓。裝修充滿懷舊風。在大堂中，掛了四隻大字，「廉而有信」。這應是她們的座右銘。
每逢上班的日子，中午十二時半已排滿了長長的人龍。若要幫趁的話，可以試試十二時。就不用花太多時間去排隊。
座位方面，樓下都算適中。但樓上座位有逼，七人只坐一張4人圓枱。環境算得上乾淨企理。員工服裝整潔。態度算是良好，有回應。上菜速度算快。
在進出門口時，小心梯級，因不很顯眼。
我試了豬棑飯，我俾3星out of 5.
又試了番茄飯，都是一般般。
飯方面略為鬆散。
港式茶餐廳 , 菠蘿油,西多士,雞批 一定要試
服務態度很差，不會再去了
